<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Freebsd on loop0</title><link>https://loop0.sh/tags/freebsd/</link><description>Recent content in Freebsd on loop0</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sun, 01 Jun 2025 20:36:10 -0400</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://loop0.sh/tags/freebsd/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Realtek 8125 2.5Gb Ethernet work on FreeBSD</title><link>https://loop0.sh/posts/freebsd-realtek-8125/</link><pubDate>Sun, 01 Jun 2025 20:36:10 -0400</pubDate><guid>https://loop0.sh/posts/freebsd-realtek-8125/</guid><description>&lt;p>I decided to migrate my virtualization host to FreeBSD bhyve.
During installation in my current hardware and one of the issues I had was the
ethernet interface not being recognized in the system. Luckily I had access
through a usb ethernet so I could run the following steps to make my onboard
network work.&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>Install the package &lt;code>realtek-re-kmod&lt;/code>:&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>pkg install realtek-re-kmod
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;ol start="2">
&lt;li>Add the following 2 lines to your &lt;code>/boot/loader.conf&lt;/code>:&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>if_re_load&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;YES&amp;#34;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>if_re_name&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>&lt;span style="color:#e6db74">&amp;#34;/boot/modules/if_re.ko&amp;#34;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;ol start="3">
&lt;li>Reboot your server&lt;/li>
&lt;li>You should be able to see the your device listed with &lt;code>ifconfig&lt;/code>&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>re0: flags&lt;span style="color:#f92672">=&lt;/span>1008943&amp;lt;UP,BROADCAST,RUNNING,PROMISC,SIMPLEX,MULTICAST,LOWER_UP&amp;gt; metric &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff">0&lt;/span> mtu &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff">1500&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;ol start="5">
&lt;li>Cheers!&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol></description></item></channel></rss>